2.8 Corollary If $f, g: X \to \overline{\mathbb{R}}$ are measurable, then so are

$$
\max \{f, g\} \quad \text{and} \quad \min \{f, g\}.
$$

2.9 Corollary If $\{f_j\}$ is a sequence of complex-valued measurable functions, and if

$$
f(x) = \lim_{j \to \infty} f_j(x) \quad \text{exists for all } x,
$$

then $f$ is measurable.

