2.18 Fatou's Lemma If $f_n \in \mathcal{L}^+$, $n = 1, 2, \ldots$, then

$$
\int \liminf_{n \to \infty} f_n \leq \liminf_{n \to \infty} \int f_n.
$$

Proof. For any $k \geq 1$,

$$
\int \left( \inf_{n \geq k} f_n \right) d\mu \leq \int f_j d\mu \quad \text{for all } j \geq k.
$$

Hence

$$
\int \left( \inf_{n \geq k} f_n \right) d\mu \leq \liminf_{j \to \infty} \int f_j d\mu.
$$

Since

$$
\inf_{n \geq k} f_n \uparrow \liminf_{n \to \infty} f_n \quad \text{as } k \to \infty,
$$

by the MCT,

$$
\int \left( \lim_{n \to \infty} \inf f_n \right) d\mu \leq \lim_{k \to \infty} \int \left( \inf_{n \geq k} f_n \right) d\mu \leq \liminf_{j \to \infty} \int f_j d\mu.
$$

