2.19 Corollary If $f_n \in \mathcal{L}^+$, $n = 1, 2, \ldots, f \in \mathcal{L}^+$ and $f_n \to f$ a.e., then

$$
\int f \, d\mu \leq \liminf_{n \to \infty} \int f_n \, d\mu.
$$

2.20 Proposition If $f \in \mathcal{L}^+$ and $\int f &lt; \infty$, then

$$
\{x: f(x) = \infty\} \text{ is a null set and } \{x: f(x) &gt; 0\} \text{ is } \sigma\text{-finite.}
$$

