2.25 Theorem Let $f_j \in L^1$, $j = 1, 2, \ldots$. Suppose

$$
\sum_{j=1}^{\infty} \int |f_j| \, d\mu &lt; \infty.
$$

Then,

$$
\sum_{j=1}^{\infty} f_j \text{ converges in } L^1, \text{ and a.e.}
$$

The limits are the same, and

$$
\int \sum_{j=1}^{\infty} f_j \, d\mu = \sum_{j=1}^{\infty} \int f_j \, d\mu.
$$

