Proof. ① Choose a sequence of partitions  $P^{(n)} = \{x_0^{(n)}, x_1^{(n)}, \ldots, x_{m_n}^{(n)}\}$  of  $[a, b]$  such that

$$
P ^ {(1)} \subset P ^ {(2)} \subset \dots , \quad \text {and} \quad \| P ^ {(n)} \| = \max  _ {1 \leq j \leq m _ {n}} \left(x _ {j} ^ {(n)} - x _ {j - 1} ^ {(n)}\right)\rightarrow 0 \text {as} n \rightarrow \infty .
$$

Let

$$
\bar {f} _ {n} = \sum_ {j = 1} ^ {m _ {n}} \sup  _ {x \in (x _ {j - 1} ^ {(n)}, x _ {j} ^ {(n)} ]} f (x) \chi_ {(x _ {j - 1} ^ {(n)}, x _ {j} ^ {(n)} ]} \quad \text{and} \quad \underline {{f}} _ {n} = \sum_ {j = 1} ^ {m _ {n}} \inf  _ {x \in (x _ {j - 1} ^ {(n)}, x _ {j} ^ {(n)} ]} f (x) \chi_ {(x _ {j - 1} ^ {(n)}, x _ {j} ^ {(n)} ]}.
$$

Then,

$$
\bar {f} _ {n} \downarrow f \quad \text {a.e.} \quad \text {and} \quad \underline {{f}} _ {n} \uparrow f \quad \text {a.e.}.
$$

By the definition of Riemann integrals and the dominated convergence theorem, we have

$$
\sum_ {j = 1} ^ {m _ {n}} \sup  _ {x \in (x _ {j - 1} ^ {(n)}, x _ {j} ^ {(n)} ]} \left(x _ {j} ^ {(n)} - x _ {j - 1} ^ {(n)}\right)\rightarrow \int_ {a} ^ {b} f (x) d x = \int_ {[ a, b ]} f d m, \quad \text {as} n \rightarrow \infty ,
$$

$$
\sum_ {j = 1} ^ {m _ {n}} \inf  _ {x \in (x _ {j - 1} ^ {(n)}, x _ {j} ^ {(n)} ]} \left(x _ {j} ^ {(n)} - x _ {j - 1} ^ {(n)}\right)\rightarrow \int_ {a} ^ {b} f (x) d x = \int_ {[ a, b ]} f d m, \quad \text {as} n \rightarrow \infty .
$$

